Quote:  Red Birch of Otago, Black Birch of Nelson, Beech, etc. (<i>Fagus Menziesi</i>), a valuable timber tree, found from the sea level to 4000 feet altitude, sometimes attaining a diameter of 12 feet.
Notes:  (Buchanan Botany Otago)

