Date:  0/0/1883
Source:  Handbook of New Zealand
Author:  HECTOR
Vol / Page:  125
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Nothofagus menziesii,</i> Hook. Tawhai, Red-birch (from the colour of the bark). --A handsome tree, 80-100 feet high; trunk 2-3 feet in diameter. The timber is chiefly used in the lake district of the South Island.
Notes:

