Vol / Page:  17/298
Edition:
Quote:   [Notho]fagus menziesii, <i>Hook. f. ... Silver Beech. Brown Birch, White Birch, Red Birch. Silver Birch. Although this species exhibits a considerable amount of variation in the shape, toothing and texture of the leaves, it is the most easily recognized of all the New Zealand beeches, especially when the fruit is fairly developed</i>
Notes:   (Kirk, NZ Beeches)

